1. Project Overview
CompTIA A+ Zero to Hero is a 90-day structured self-study web application for passing the CompTIA A+ certification exams. It features:
    • 90 structured study days covering both Core 1 and Core 2 objectives
    • Embedded Professor Messer video lessons (YouTube)
    • Per-day checklists, note-taking objectives, acronym drills
    • 240 practice questions across 12 test sets (6 Core 1 + 6 Core 2)
    • Full glossary/notes reference with search
    • Gamification: XP, levels, achievements, streaks
    • Dark mode, notifications, cloud sync via Google Apps Script
    • Multi-user authentication (GAS-backed or local fallback)
The app is a 3-file static web app — no server, no build step, no npm. Deploy by serving the three files from any web server or opening index.html locally.

2. File Structure
comptia-app/
├── index.html          # HTML shell: layout, nav, modals, auth overlay
├── styles.css          # All CSS: layout, components, dark mode, new topic styles
├── data.js             # All data: PHASES, DAYS, VIDEO_SEARCHES, TESTS,
│                       #           ABBREVS, EXTRA, ALL_NOTES, DAY_NOTES,
│                       #           NEW_TESTS, NEW_ABBREVS (new 1201/1202 content)
├── app.js              # All JavaScript logic: auth, gamification, UI, quiz engine
└── DOCUMENTATION.md    # This file
Load order matters: data.js must load before app.js since app.js reads constants defined in data.js. The HTML loads them in the correct order.

