6. data.js
Overview
The largest file (~2,844 lines). Contains all study content as JavaScript constants in global scope. All constants are const declarations — no IIFE wrapping.
Data Structures
PHASES (Array)
Defines the 6 study phases and their day ranges:
const PHASES = [
  {id:'c1',   label:'Core 1',        days:[1,40],  cls:'c1'},
  {id:'c1r',  label:'Core 1 Review', days:[41,45], cls:'c1r'},
  {id:'c2',   label:'Core 2',        days:[46,80], cls:'c2'},
  {id:'c2r',  label:'Core 2 Review', days:[81,85], cls:'c2r'},
  {id:'pbq',  label:'PBQ Sprint',    days:[86,89], cls:'pbq'},
  {id:'final',label:'Final Audit',   days:[90,90], cls:'final'}
];
DAYS (Array, 90 items)
Each day object:
{
  day: 1,                          // Day number (1-90)
  topic: "string",                 // Day title (shown in sidebar and day header)
  links: [{label:"", url:""}],     // External resource links
  checklist: ["item1", "item2"],   // Task list items (+2 XP each when checked)
  note: "string",                  // Note-taking objective prompt
  practice: "KEY=val | KEY2=val2"  // Pipe-separated acronym/term pairs for chips
}
VIDEO_SEARCHES (Object)
Maps day numbers to Professor Messer YouTube video IDs:
const VIDEO_SEARCHES = {
  "1": [{id: "T8UQp6lD9eo", title: "How to Pass 220-1201 & 220-1202"}],
  "2": [{id: "BpKw2u_aDzo", title: "Motherboard Form Factors"}, ...],
  ...
}
TESTS (Object)
Contains two arrays: TESTS.core1 and TESTS.core2. Each is an array of test sets:
const TESTS = {
  core1: [
    {
      title: "Core 1 (220-1201) — Set 1: Hardware & Components",
      questions: [
        {
          q: "Question text",
          opts: ["A", "B", "C", "D"],
          ans: 2,           // 0-indexed correct answer
          exp: "Explanation shown after answering"
        },
        ...  // 20 questions per set
      ]
    },
    ...  // 6 sets total (Sets 1-5 original + Set 6 new 1201 content)
  ],
  core2: [...]  // Same structure, 6 sets
};
After the NEW_TESTS block in data.js, the new sets are merged:
TESTS.core1.push(...NEW_TESTS.core1_new);
TESTS.core2.push(...NEW_TESTS.core2_new);
ABBREVS and EXTRA (Arrays)
Reference tables for the Notes tab. Each item:
{
  title: "Section Title",
  items: [["Term", "Definition"], ...]
}
ALL_NOTES = [...ABBREVS, ...EXTRA] merges both for the notes tab.
DAY_NOTES (Object)
HTML string content for each day's "Class Notes" card:
const DAY_NOTES = {
  1: `<h3>Title</h3><p>Content...</p>`,
  2: `...`,
  ...
}
New content is injected via Object.assign(DAY_NOTES, {...}) at the bottom of data.js. Day notes for days 1, 11, 21, 29, 32, 34 have new 1201/1202 content appended.
NEW_ABBREVS (Array)
Two new sections added to ALL_NOTES:
    • "220-1201 — New Core 1 Topics" — 17 new terms
    • "220-1202 — New Core 2 Topics" — 20 new terms

