Gamification System
    • XP: +50 per day completed, +2 per checklist item, +10 per correct quiz answer, +25/+50 bonus for 80%+/100% quiz scores
    • Levels: Every 500 XP = 1 level
    • Achievements: 14 defined in ACHS array (first day, 7-day streak, perfect score, etc.)
    • Streak: Consecutive days with at least one completed activity, tracked via localStorage.cpt_dates
Authentication
The app supports two modes:
    1. Cloud mode (GAS): If GAS_URL is configured, login/register/progress sync via Google Apps Script
    2. Local mode: Falls back to localStorage if GAS is unreachable or not configured
    3. Guest mode: skipLogin() creates a guest account with local-only storage
User data is stored with user-scoped keys: cpt_{username}_{datatype} (e.g., cpt_john_done).

8. Deployment Guide
Option A: Local Use (Simplest)
    1. Place index.html, styles.css, data.js, app.js in the same folder
    2. Open index.html in any modern browser
    3. Progress saves to localStorage (browser-specific)
Note: YouTube embeds may not work with file:// protocol in some browsers. Use a local server for full functionality.
Option B: Local Server (Recommended for Development)
# Python 3
python3 -m http.server 8080

# Node.js
npx serve .

# VS Code: Install Live Server extension, click "Go Live"
Then open http://localhost:8080
Option C: Static Hosting (Production)
Upload all 4 files to any static host:
    • GitHub Pages: Push to repo, enable Pages
    • Netlify: Drag-and-drop the folder
    • Vercel: vercel deploy
    • Your own web server: Copy files to /var/www/html/
No build process, no dependencies, no Node.js required.
Option D: Android APK (Capacitor)
The app was previously wrapped with Capacitor for Android:
com.touhid.comptiaplus
Min SDK: 24 (Android 7.0)
Target SDK: 36
Capacitor: 8.3.0
See original build scripts for Capacitor setup. The web app works in mobile browsers without an APK.

9. Configuration
Google Apps Script Cloud Sync
To enable cloud sync (multi-device progress), deploy a Google Apps Script:
    1. Open script.google.com → New project
    2. Implement doGet(e) and doPost(e) handlers for actions:
        ◦ login — verify username/password hash, return user data
        ◦ register — create new user record
        ◦ saveProgress — save done/subs/xp/ach/scores to Sheets
    3. Deploy as Web App (anyone can access)
    4. In app.js, update:
const GAS_URL = 'https://script.google.com/macros/s/YOUR_DEPLOYMENT_ID/exec';
The existing GAS URL in the app is a pre-configured backend — replace with your own for a private deployment.
Customizing the GAS URL
The GAS URL is in app.js at approximately line 537:
const GAS_URL = 'https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycb.../exec';
Set to '' or 'YOUR_GAS_WEB_APP_URL_HERE' to disable cloud sync and use local-only mode.

10. Data Architecture
localStorage Key Schema
All keys prefixed with cpt_ (global) or cpt_{username}_ (user-scoped):
Key	Type	Content
cpt_current_user	JSON	{username, name, prefix}
cpt_users	JSON	{username: {name, hash, prefix, created}}
cpt_{prefix}_done	JSON	Array of completed day numbers
cpt_{prefix}_subs	JSON	{"dayIdx_checkIdx": true}
cpt_{prefix}_xp	String	Total XP number
cpt_{prefix}_ach	JSON	Array of earned achievement IDs
cpt_{prefix}_scores	JSON	{"c1_0": 18, "c2_3": 20, ...}
cpt_{prefix}_notif_on	String	"1" or "0"
cpt_{prefix}_notif_time	String	"HH:MM"
cpt_{prefix}_notifications	JSON	Array of notification objects
cpt_{prefix}_last_seen	String	Last visit date string
cpt_dates	JSON	Array of date strings (for streak)
cpt_lastdate	String	Last activity date
cpt_darkmode	String	"1" or "0"
cpt_level	String	Current level number
cpt_streak_shown	String	Date streak modal was last shown

Data Flow
User action → UI event → app.js function
→ Update in-memory state (completed, totalXP, etc.)
→ save() → localStorage (immediate) + gasCall() (debounced 2s)
→ updateStats() → DOM updates

11. Feature Reference
Study Day Card Sections (in order)
    1. Day Header — phase badge, title, day number, exam series label
    2. Professor Messer Video — embedded YouTube (privacy-enhanced mode), tab switcher if multiple videos
    3. Class Notes — HTML notes from DAY_NOTES[d], includes new AI/Zero Trust callouts for relevant days
    4. Today's Checklist — interactive checkboxes (+2 XP each)
    5. Note-Taking Objective — prompt question for self-study notes
    6. Acronyms & Terms — clickable chip-style term/definition pairs
    7. External Resources — links to Professor Messer, ExamCompass, Crucial Exams, CompTIA.org
    8. Complete Row — "Mark Day Complete" button + Prev/Next navigation
Notes Tab
    • Searchable via real-time text filter (filterNotes())
    • Shows all sections from ALL_NOTES (ABBREVS + EXTRA + NEW_ABBREVS)
    • Search covers both term and definition columns
    • Empty sections auto-hide when filtered
Tests Tab
    • 12 test sets total (6 Core 1, 6 Core 2) × 20 questions = 240 questions
    • Sets 1-5 cover original 220-1101/1102 content (still valid for 1201/1202)
    • Set 6 covers new 220-1201/1202 specific objectives
    • Keyboard shortcut: press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to answer while in quiz
    • Each correct answer shows explanation immediately
    • Results card shows score, XP earned, performance message
Dark Mode
    • Persists in localStorage.cpt_darkmode
    • Applied at document level: html.dark-mode
    • All colors use CSS variables so dark mode is purely CSS
    • System preference not automatically applied — must be toggled manually
Notifications
    • Uses browser Notification API (permission required)
    • Daily reminder at configurable time (default 09:00)
    • In-app notification feed (bell icon, red badge)
    • Notifications persist per user in localStorage

12. Extending the App
Adding a New Test Set
In data.js, add to TESTS.core1 or TESTS.core2:
TESTS.core1.push({
  title: "Core 1 (220-1201) — Set 7: Advanced Topics",
  questions: [
    {q: "...", opts: ["A","B","C","D"], ans: 0, exp: "..."},
    // ... 20 questions recommended
  ]
});
Adding New Notes Sections
In data.js, push to ALL_NOTES:
ALL_NOTES.push({
  title: "My New Topic Section",
  items: [
    ["Term", "Definition"],
    ["Term2", "Definition2"]
  ]
});
Adding New Day Notes
In data.js, add to DAY_NOTES or extend existing entries:
DAY_NOTES[15] = DAY_NOTES[15] + `
<div class="ai-note">
  <strong>New content:</strong> Your HTML here...
</div>`;
Modifying a Study Day
Edit the corresponding entry in the DAYS array in data.js. Each day has: day, topic, links, checklist, note, practice.
Adding a New Achievement
In app.js, add to the ACHS array:
{id:'custom1', icon:'🎯', name:'My Achievement', desc:'Description',
 check:()=> /* condition returning true/false */ }
Updating the GAS Backend
The app communicates with GAS via URL parameters for GET and form data for POST. Actions:
    • login — params: username, password (hashed)
    • register — params: username, name, password
    • saveProgress — params: username, done, subs, xp, ach, scores
GAS returns JSON: {ok: true/false, data: {...}, error: "message"}.

